value_old: A pathologic tract that connects an opening in the anal canal to the perianal skin. In the vast majority of cases there is a history of perianal abscess.
value_new: An intestinal disorder characterized by an opening in the anal canal to the perianal skin. In the vast majority of cases there is a history of perianal abscess.

value_old: Any early infantile epileptic encephalopathy in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the DNM1 gene.
value_new: Any developmental and epileptic encephalopathy in which the cause of the disease is a heterozygous mutation in the DNM1 gene.
Any developmental and epileptic encephalopathy in which the cause of the disease is a homozygous mutation in the DNM1 gene.
